comment: Jordan (LAC) establishes a legal screening position in Iguodala's (GSW) path, giving him the opportunity to avoid the contact. When the contact occurs, Jordan absorbs it.
Iguodala (GSW) makes contact with Jordan's (LAC) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Iguodala (GSW) makes contact with Jordan's (LAC) wrist that affects his ability to secure the rebound.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Iguodala (GSW) was overturned and GSW was awarded possession.
Rivers (LAC) grabs Iguodala (GSW) from behind and affects his ability to catch the pass.

LHH clearly shows Griffin (LAC) gather the ball while in the air, landing on both feet. He establishes his right foot as his pivot by stepping with his left across his body, and then begins his drive when he brings his left foot forward again.
LATR shows Iguodala (GSW) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly strips the ball from Griffin (LAC).

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Griffin (LAC) was overturned and the Clippers were awarded possession due to the ball hitting Iguodala's (GSW) foot prior to going OOB.
Iguodala (GSW) and Griffin (LAC) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Griffin (LAC) makes contact with Curry (GSW) after he secures the rebound.
Griffin (LAC) commits a take foul on Thompson (GSW).
L-Slash and LATR shows Thompson (GSW) maintains legal guarding position as he blocks Crawford's (LAC) shot attempt.
